name: Pondok Genyol Bu Agus Family Sading Cabang Sempidi
address: Jl. Langon No.12, Sempidi, Kec. Mengwi, Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80116, Indonesia
review 1:
"Not bad, but it would be better without that dog."

So, my friend, I went to this place the other day. Oh yeah, the babi guling there is decent, but not exactly amazing. I've had much tastier dishes in Ubud, to be honest. This option is just... well, mediocre, you know?

The staff seemed friendly enough, but on the other hand, they also seemed a bit indifferent, not entirely interested in making sure you have a good time. I don't know, maybe I'm too demanding, but still.

The atmosphere in the cafe was okay overall, but man, there was this clingy dog... It totally threw me off track. I was trying to enjoy my babi guling, but the dog kept coming up and distracting me. I don't know, maybe some people like that, but I don't.

In general, I wouldn't say that this place is bad, but it's not exactly super either. If it weren't for the dog and a bit more care from the staff, maybe I would recommend it. But for now, you know, it's better to look for other places in the area. Just in case.
review 2: I found my favorite balinese sausage (Urutan) and some delicious crispy pork skin, the whole taste is so so. It's affordable price to dine in with green view.
review 3: Love the place, great food, good service. üëç
review 4: Yes! Last year I went to Bali, my dad suggested us to go here and that was truly the best decision. I am in love with their nasi genyol special. Even the place is quite cozy. 100% recommend.
review 5: Good taste of pork with balinese spicy...you can try if you past this street...

name: Berkah Vegan
address: Jl. Raya Sempidi Badung No.1, Dalung, Kec. Kuta Utara, Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80351, Indonesia
review 1:
Good vegan take on a Balinese Nasi Campur, run by the same movement that owns the Loving Hut.

Better to buy for takeaway since the venue is located facing a main road that gets loud and produces lots of fumes.
review 2: Berkah Vegan is a delightful rare hidden gem conveniently located in Bali. The menu is completely vegan and full of a wide assortment of delicious foods. You can ask for a plate and try all of their daily specials. The food is mouthwatering and simply healthy. You will love the variety of options. The team here is super friendly and super full of love! Ketut helped me pick the perfect food. He is very kind and full of lots of wisdom and knowledge. You will love the clean environment and easy location to find! The team is super helpful and very warm. This is a must try for a vegans and non-vegans. You will love everything here! Do not miss this place in Bali! Good vibes only! üôè
review 3: We absolutely LOVED this place. We came back most days for lunch and then again for dinner. The food is good quality, Balinese vegan food, and it is really affordable. We loved the fact there were vegan cakes and sweet foods. Suksma, see you next time ü•∞
review 4: Very good vegan food. All vegan food with the Balinese taste. Allot of choice, I will definitely eat there many more times during my stay here. Good price. And very nice people as well
review 5: Delicious and cheap vegan food, big portion, siobak veru good, nasi campur also very good, alot of choice in dishes

I tried their speciality food: Chicken Mixed Rice with Chicken broth. The portion is suitable for me! The rice and the toppings on plate was sweet and the additional chicken broth complete the taste with a bit spicy aftertaste.
The resto located right beside the main road and don't have parking lot, so you will have to park your vehicle on the side of the street.
The price: affordable and you can split bill even if you come in group.
Worth to try!
